Realistic morning routine: toddler mom + 5 months pregnant ☀️☕️

Allie wakes up at 7am so I try to get up an hour before her to reset the kitchen, fluff / fold laundry, and have some “me time” before the chaos of the day begins!!

Normally I start work at 9am but this was filmed during holiday break! Had a prenatal massage (Christmas gift from Jerome) and chiro appointment instead 🥰🥰

✨ Bought a house and moved from LA to San Diego (only 10 min from Jerome’s parents)

Going to the beach for the first time with 2 under 2 🥺

…We almost didn’t go. I was overwhelmed with everything we needed to pack, what could go wrong, how I needed to prepare.

Then my aunt reminded me:  Take it all with a grain of sand 🤣 Be present in the moment. Enjoy it, you’ll never have a first time for you all to go to the beach again! 

…So we did. And I’ll forever cherish this perfectly imperfect first trip to the beach as a family of 4. 🩵

✨FAMILY FUN DAY VLOG✨ at the San Diego Children’s Discovery Museum!

We started a new tradition to get out of the house on the weekends and take the kids somewhere fun to create memories, because we’ve realized we have to be intentional with this — if you don’t plan it, it won’t happen! 

So thankful we live in a fun and beautiful city that has so much to offer. San Diego friends: where should we go next?! 🩷🛝🎡🎠🎢🎟️🐬☀️

#sandiegomoms #northcountysd #socalmoms #thingstodoinsandiego

Wise words from @monicaswanson_ 💛 Her book #RaisingAmazing has completely rocked me and I urge you to check it out if you need some encouragement during this season 🫶🏽✨

We can be both honest about the struggles of parenting and courageous to keep doing our best in the midst of them. 

We can laugh at life’s craziness while taking our role as parents seriously. 

We can parent with the dignity our high calling deserves. 

I know the days can be very, very long, but one day you’ll see this season of raising kids for what it is: short.

We love it though lol 😌 Forever Jessica ✨P✨

🛝ATTN PARENTS: We learned the hard way 😩 and now I’ve heard just how common this injury is!!! Our 2 year old broke her ankle (2 hairline fractures) going down the big slide with daddy because her shoe got caught on the side. 🥺 Even if you try to keep their little legs tucked in, that doesn’t always work, so just take off their shoes!!! I wish someone had told me this sooner 😅🥲🫶🏽
